# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package
# Tutorial 10 (visualization): render the diamond structure of silicon.
#
# The diamond lattice is two interpenetrating fcc sublattices, offset by
# (1/4,1/4,1/4).  We build them as two atom types so the two sublattices --
# the two atoms of the basis that give rise to the optical branches -- can be
# drawn in two shades.  Both are silicon (one element).

units       metal
atom_style  atomic
boundary    p p p

variable    a0 equal 5.4309
lattice     fcc ${a0}
region      box block 0 2 0 2 0 2
create_box  2 box
create_atoms 1 box                          # sublattice A
lattice     fcc ${a0} origin 0.25 0.25 0.25
create_atoms 2 box                          # sublattice B
mass        1 28.0855
mass        2 28.0855
pair_style  sw
pair_coeff  * * Si.sw Si Si
neighbor    1.0 bin
run         0                               # build a neighbor list for autobond

# ball-and-stick: spheres + bonds inferred from the neighbor list (autobond)
write_dump  all image si-diamond.png type type adiam 1.6 autobond 2.7 0.4 &
            view 55 25 zoom 1.2 size 1000 950                            &
            shiny 0.2 fsaa yes ssao yes 9135 0.55 box yes 0.02            &
            modify backcolor white boxcolor midnightblue                  &
            color darkgold 0.72 0.46 0.10 acolor 1 goldenrod acolor 2 darkgold
